model_solution:
Step 1:  Start by simplifying the given expression, $\frac{\csc \theta}{\sin \theta} - \frac{\cot \theta}{\tan \theta}$. 
$\frac{\csc \theta}{\sin \theta} - \frac{\cot \theta}{\tan \theta} = \frac{1}{\sin \theta} \cdot \frac{\sin \theta}{\csc \theta} - \frac{\cos \theta}{\sin \theta} \cdot \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta}$
Step 2: 
$\frac{1}{\sin \theta} \cdot \frac{\sin \theta}{\csc \theta} - \frac{\cos \theta}{\sin \theta} \cdot \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta} = \frac{1}{\csc \theta} - \frac{\cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$\frac{1}{\csc \theta} - \frac{\cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin \theta}{1} - \frac{\cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$\frac{\sin \theta}{1} - \frac{\cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^3 \theta - \cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$\frac{\sin^3 \theta - \cos^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^3 \theta - (1 - \sin^2 \theta)}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$= \frac{\sin^3 \theta - 1 + \sin^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$\frac{\sin^3 \theta - 1 + \sin^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta(\sin \theta - 1) + 1}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$\frac{\sin^2 \theta(\sin \theta - 1) + 1}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta(\sin \theta - 1) + 1}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta \sin \theta - \sin^3 \theta + 1}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$\frac{\sin^2 \theta \sin \theta - \sin^3 \theta + 1}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta \sin \theta - \sin^2 \theta \sin \theta + 1}{\sin^2 \theta}$
$\frac{\sin^2 \theta \sin \theta - \sin^2 \theta \sin \theta + 1}{\sin^2 \theta} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta (\sin \theta - \sin \theta) + 1}{\sin^2 \theta}$
